The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 February is 38,757 (4,485.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 February, there were 1,223 new confirmed cases (141.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 February, there were 1,799 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (576 fewer cases).
